documents.s: Installation, Activate and Upgrade of Bit Integrations

documents.t: Follow the path mentioned below: At first, navigate to your wordpress & navigate to plugin. Then click on Add new. Go to search option & search Bit Integrations. Click Install now & then Activate free version. Now you can see Bit Integrations in your WordPress plugin list. After successful installation you can see the home page of Bit Integrations'. Now You are ready to create Integration.

At first go to our website bitapps.pro/bit-integrations Go to Pricing section of pro version. Now you can see all the plans of Bit Integrations. Select your desired plan & you can customize the quantity of sites. Click on Proceed. You have to fill up the form for membership account to use the premium version of Bit Integrations. Give your location & payment information. Pay the amount via any credit card or PayPal. Also can use coupon card if you have any. After you will be redirected to subscription page. You can check your subscription is activated or not by reloading the page. After you will be notified via your email with download link , license key, tutorial link & documentation link. Now, go to your subscription dashboard. Here you can see your subscription details. You can also update your plans at any time. Download the pro version by clicking the option. Then go to your WordPress dashboard & again navigate to plugin option. Click on Add New & select upload plugin. Click on Choose File & select the zip file you have downloaded before. Then click on Install Now. Then press on Activate Plugin. After you will see the pro version of Bit Integrations on your plugin list. Then go to Bit Integrations from dashboard & you will find license option. And now copy the key from subscription page & paste the key on license key option. After clicking Submit button you will be shown a successful message. Congratulations! Now you are a pro member of the Bit Integrations. Now you can access pro features, updates & support.

Bit Integrations have some options in every integration called Info Edit Timeline Clone Delete. Please follow the points below to know how these options work 1. Info: You can see the Authorized process information. E.g., What were the Client ID and Secret or API Key for the authorization process. 2. Edit: You can edit the integration you have already set up. If you want to make some necessary changes, you can do it by editing the integration. 4. Clone: You can Clone the integration you had already set up. Suppose you already set up an integration Contact Form 7 with Google Sheet. And now you want to Integrate with another sheet. If you Clone the integration, you can save some time without having to repeat the authorize process. Note: This feature (Clone) is available in pro version 5. Delete: If you don't need any integration that you set up, you can delete this integration by deleting this option.

Note: Autonami is only available on the pro version. Search & Autonami from the actions pages. Before setting up the integration, you must confirm that the Autonami Pro plugin is activated on your site. Otherwise, the integration will not work. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “Autonami”. Now click on the Connect to Autonami button to complete authorization settings. Then Click on Next button. After completing the authorization process, select the contacts list that you have created before on Autonami. You can choose multiple lists from here. You can add a Tag [ also multiple tags] for the contacts that you have created before on your Autonami account. Your Autonami plugin must already have tags. Then you have to map the form fields with Autonami fields. By default, the field is Email. Also, you set any field required on Autonami, and it will be automatically displayed on your map settings. You can set multiple fields from map field settings.

If the contact already exists in Autonami. It will be skip contact; otherwise, it will update the contact based on email address. After clicking Finish & Save you can see the integration you have created now. We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: Dropbox is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Dropbox from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken ‘Dropbox Integration’. After that, To get the API key & API Secret, click on Dropbox API Console. Choose an API: Scoped access Choose the type of access you need: Full Dropbox Type Name your app and click on Create App button. Go to Permissions Tab: Permissions that allow your app to view and manage > you need to enable all scopes. Now copy the API key and API secret, then paste it into the integration’s dashboard. After that, to get the Access Code, click on Dropbox Access Code. And Create a Access Code. Now copy the Generated Access Code and paste it into the integration’s dashboard. And Click on “Authorize” button. Click on Next to set up the other integration settings ahead. After completing the authorization process, you will find the Map Field option. Select the folder Name from the Drop-Down list that you want to send the files to the folder. Also, if you want to delete the uploaded file from WordPress, enable the 'Delete File From WordPress' option.

Now click on Next button. And save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button. We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone and Delete the integration.

Note: Elastic Email is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Elastic Email from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken Elastic Email. After that, To get the API key, click on Elastic Email API Console or Login your Elastic Email dashboard => click on My Account => Setting => Create Additional API Key . You need to grant Full Access permission to make the API successful. Now copy the API key and paste it into the integrations dashboard. And Click on “Authorize” button Click on Next to set up the other integration settings ahead. After completing the authorization process, Select the List from the drop-down option. You have to create a list before on your Elastic Email account. You will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related Elastic Email field. Here ‘Email‘ field is the default for Elastic Email. Now, click on the Next button to move forward for further settings. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone Delete the integration.

Note: Fluent CRM is only available on the pro version. Search & Select FluentCRM from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken 'FluentCRM'. Click on the Connect to Fluent CRM button. info Note: Before setting up the integration, you must confirm that the Fluent CRM plugin is activated on your site. Otherwise, the integration will not work. Click on Next to set up the other integration settings ahead.

After completing the authorization process, Select the FluentCRM list on the Fluent CRM field that you have created before on your CRM account. All your subscribers will be listed under this list. You can select multiple tags for the list on the FluentCRM Tags field. You have to create them earlier on the FluentCRM. Tags will help you to search the list & leads easily. Then, you have to map the form fields with FluentCRM fields. By default, the field is Email. You can select multiple fields from map field settings. There are two actions available you can trigger if you need any of them- Skip exist contact: Enabling this option, you can skip duplicate email submission of the subscriber. Double Opt-in: If this action is enabled, then the user will get a notification if they want to be a subscriber or not. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone Delete the integration.

Note: Freshdesk is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Freshdesk from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken 'Freshdesk'. Your App Domain and App API key: To get App Domain and API go to your Freshdesk account. Copy the App Domain from the URL and paste it into Your App Domain Field. To get the API key to navigate to your Freshdesk Profile settings. There you will find the API key on top-right. Copy the API key And paste it into App API key field in integration settings. Now click on Authorize Button after successfully authorizing click on the Next button. Then you will see the map fields option and map all fields mandatory with the corresponding fields in your form/task. Map all the mandatory Freshdesk fields to the corresponding fields in your form/task. Show contact field: Also you can map Freshdesk contact with your form/task field by enabling this option. And you have to map all the mandatory with corresponding fields.

Status: Status is mandatory in Freshdesk. You have to select the status from actions Priority: Also Priority is mandatory in Freshdesk. You have to select the status from actions. Photo: You can add any contact’s profile photo Ticket profile photo through our Bit Integration to your Freshdesk. For that, hoover on the action called “Photo“. After mapping the relevant field, click the action ‘Photp’ to upload a photo from Form/Task to your Freshdesk. The image will be automatically uploaded as a profile photo to the Freshdesk contact’s or Ticket. File: This action sends attachments from your Form/Task to Freshdesk. After mapping the relevant fields, click the action ‘File‘ to send any file from your Form/Task to Freshdesk. Now click on ‘Save’. You can now directly check the file attachments from your Freshdesk. Update: You can also update the submitted data by enabling the action called Update. Suppose the user already submitted data under an email address. Again they want to submit data under the same email, if the action is enabled then the new data will be updated regarding that email address. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: Google Calendar is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Google Calendar from the actions pages. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “Google Sheet”. Client ID & Secret: For client ID & secret you have to visit the Google API console. If you already have any Client ID & secret before then copy this to the field. If you don’t have any then you have to create a new client ID & secret. If you don’t have any then you have to create a new client ID & secret. Client ID & Secret: For client ID & secret, you have to visit the Google API console. If you already have any Client ID & secret before then, copy this to the field. If you don't have any, then you have to create a new client ID & secret To create Google OAuth-2, you have to visit the Google API console. If you don't have any Projects in Google Console, you have to create projects in Console. To create a Project, click on My First Project -> Then Click New Project. In the Project name field, put the Project name of your choices. If you have any Organization for the Location field, you can put your Organization or leave it as default. Now click on the "Create" button to create a Project. Now go to the Google API Console Dashboard, and you have to enable Google sheets API and Google Calendar API. To enable Google Sheets API and Google Calendar API to go to Dashboard and select ENABLE APIS AND SERVICE. Search Google Calendar API in this search bar. Now Select Google Calendar API and enable API by clicking on the "Enable" button. If you have already created an application under OAuth Consent Screen, or you have to create an application. And select the Scopes tab, and you have to add Google Sheets API and Google Calendar API scopes. To add Google Sheets API and Google Calendar API scopes. Click on the "ADD OR REMOVE SCOPES" button. Then search and add Google Sheets API and Google Calendar API scopes and click on the "Update" button. After complete these steps, to get new Client Id & Client secret information go to Google API CONSOL=> Credentials=>Create Credentials=> OAuth Client ID => Select Application Type=> Give a Client Name => Add home page URL => Add authorized URL. Register all the information and get your client ID & Secret information from google sheet. Now give Client ID & Secret to the fields & click Authorize & you are ready to import all your data from Bit Form to your Google Sheet. Now select the Calendar Lists and Time Zone from drop-down list of your choice You can now map the Bit form fields with the necessary Google fields. You can send custom values on Google Sheet. After mapping the desired fields, click on Next.

1.All Day Event: By enabling this action, Events will create without time range. The Event will create for a full day. 2.Skip If Slot Not Free: By enabling this action, Event create will skip if the slot is not free. Suppose you have three slots in a day at the specific time range. If these three slot time ranges coincide with the current event created then the event will not be created it will skip. The event will skip if the slot time range matches the event deadline. 3. Set Reminders: By enabling this option you can set a reminder with an Email and Calendar Notification. Also, you can set a time, how long ago you want to get the reminder. Note: You have to set a reminder to get reminder from drop-down list.
To save the integration process click on Finish & Save. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

documents.t: Note: Post Creation is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Post Creation from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken 'Post Creation'. After navigate to the integration page, select the Post Type you have created for the integration. For example, we have selected Photo Album as custom post type. Now, select Post Status, Author & Comment Status according to the requirement. For the field mapping option, map the form fields with the general/default post fields. Click on Next to set up the other integration settings ahead. For the field mapping option, you need to configure two types of mapping of two popular plugins (ACF, Meta Box) as needed - Then map the form fields with the related ACF or Meta Box fields. Lastly map the file upload field. Click on the Next button to move forward for further settings. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button. We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone Delete the integration.

Note: User Registration is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Registration from the actions pages. You have to map Trigger fields with WP default user fields. For a successful full registration there are two types of notifications - User Email Notification & Admin Email Notification. Also, WP admin can set the WP User Role. And you can set auto Login, the user login automatically after registration. Additionally, you can add custom fields to personalize your users' profile. You can create custom fields. After creating custom fields, you have to map it with Trigger fields from the User Meta Field Mapping. For that you need the corresponding id of the custom field. info Note: If the Username and Password fields are blank then the user will take the value of the email field as the field and the password will be auto-generated. Now save the integration by clicking the Save Button. We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone Delete the integration.

Note: Sendinblue is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Sendinblue from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “Sendinblue”. API Key: You have to copy the key from the Sendinblue dashboard & paste the key on the field. If you don’t have any create a new one. To get a new API key, go to Sendinblue API CONSOL=> SMTP & API=> Create a new API key. Register all the information and get your API key. Now click Authorize & you are ready to integrate with your Sendinblue account. Select the list from the drop-down option. You have to create a list on the Sendinblue dashboard & that will show on the drop-down list. Also, you can select multiple lists. When you fill-up the contact list field, you will find the Map Field option. Map all the mandatory CRM fields to the corresponding fields in your form/task.

You can also update the submitted data by enabling the action called Update Sendinblue. Suppose the user already submitted data under an email address. Again they want to submit data under the same email, if the action is enabled then the new data will be updated regarding that email address. Now save the integration by clicking the "Finish & Save." Button We have an option in every integration "Timeline" where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: Slack is available on the free and pro version. Search & Select Slack from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken 'Slack'. After that, you have to copy the API key from your Slack account & paste the key on the field. To get the API key, click on Slack API Console or go to api.slack.com/apps Setup Proccess click on Create New App/Create an App: From scratch. Type your app name Select your workspace from the Drop-Down list that you want to send the message. and click on Create App button. In the left sidebar menu, navigate to OAuth & Permissions tab under Features. Scroll Down and go to User Token Scopes under scopes section and add scopes chat:write, channels:read, channels:write, files:read, files:write. Go to OAuth Tokens for Your Workspace section and click on install to workspace button. Now copy the API key and paste it into the integrations dashboard. And Click on “Authorize” button. Click on Next to set up the other integration settings ahead. After completing the authorization process, Select the Channels List from the drop-down option. You have to create a list before on your Slack account. You can design your message in two ways HTML Markdown v2.
You can put dynamic field names email body. You can copy and paste previous design template another editor. You can edit styling by the help of rich text editor.
You can put dynamic field names email body. You can edit messages as wish.

You can select the action Attachment right below the Message’ field. Enabling this action, you can send – Audio, Video, Photo, or Document from Trigger to slack. After this, click on the Next option. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone Delete the integration.

Note: Trello is available on the free and pro version. Search & Select Trello from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken 'Trello'. After that, to get the API key, click on Trello API Console Setup Process Copy Authorized Redirect URIs Scroll down and go to 'Allowed Origins' section, paste ‘New Allowed Origin’ field. Click on Submit button Now copy the API key and paste it into the integration’s dashboard. And Click on “Authorize” button. Click on Next to set up the other integration settings ahead. After completing the authorization process, Select the Boards from the drop-down option. You have to create a Boards before on your trello account. And select the list form the drop-down option. You will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related Trello Board field. Here ‘Name ‘field is the default for Trello Board.

If you enable this option. You can display your message at the top or bottom of the list as you wish. Now, click on the Next button to move forward for further settings. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone Delete the integration.

Note: Tutor LMS is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Tutor LMS from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “Tutor LMS ”. Now click on the Connect Button to connect with Tutor LMS; after successfully connect, click on the Next button. Select the Action (Enroll the user in a course, Unenroll user from a course, Mark a course complete for the user, Mark a lesson complete for the user, Reset the user progress in a course) from the Drop-Down list, And Select the Course/ Lessons from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with Tutor LMS . Then click on the Next button. Now save the integration by clicking the "Finish & Save." Button

Search & Select WP Courseware from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “WP Courseware ”. Now click on the Connect Button to connect with WP Courseware; after successfully connect, click on the Next button. Select the Action (Enroll the user in a course, Unenroll user from a course) from the Drop-Down list, And Select the Course/ Lessons from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with WP Courseware . Then click on the Next button. Now save the integration by clicking the "Finish & Save." Button

Note: Active Campaign is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Active Campaign from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “ActiveCampaign”. Access API URL & API key: To get the URL & key : log in to ActiveCampaign dashboard=> Settings=> Developer=> Get your API URL & Key.You have to copy the API URL & Key from the Active Campaign Developer section & paste the URL & key on the fields of integration settings. Now click Authorize, & you are ready to integrate with your ActiveCampaign account. After successful authorization. Select the List from the drop-down option. You have to create a list before on your ActiveCampaign account. You can add a Tag [ also multiple tags] for the Contacts that you have created before on your ActiveCampaign account You will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related ActiveCampaign field. Here ‘Email‘ field is the default for ActiveCampaign.

You can also update the submitted data by enabling the action called Update ActiveCampaign. Suppose the user already submitted data under an email address. Again they want to submit data under the same email, if the action is enabled, then the new data will be updated regarding that email address. Now save the integration by clicking the "Finish & Save." Button We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: MailChimp is available on the free and pro version. Search & Select MailChimp from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “Mailchimp”. Client ID & Client Secret: To get new Client Id & Client secret go to Mailchimp API CONSOLE > Register An App. In the App website & Redirect URL fields you have to give the values of the field of Homepage URL & Authorized Redirect URL respectively. Now, click on the “Create” button. You have to copy the Client ID & Client secret from MailChimp & paste the Client ID & Client secret on the fields of integration settings. And click on the "Authorize" button. Select the audience from the drop-down option. You have to create an audience before on your Mailchimp account. You can add a Tag [ also multiple tags] for the audience that you have created before on your MailChimp account. When you fill-up the audience list field, you will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related Mailchimp field.

Also, you can enable the action Add Address Field to add the address of the contact. The addresses fields of Mailchimp are fixed – Address, City, Zip & State. These fields are required for the Mailchimp audience. By enabling the action Double-Opt-in admin can ask permission from users if they want to subscribe to MailChimp or not. You can also update the submitted data by enabling the action called Update Mailchimp. Suppose the user already submitted data under an email address. Again they want to submit data under the same email, if the action is enabled then the new data will be updated regarding that email address.
After clicking on Finish & Save, the Mailchimp integration is ready. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: Telegram is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Telegram from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Telegram”. To get the API Key, visit your telegram account. Now, search for @BotFather. If you have created a bot before, then just copy the API key & past the key on the API Key field on the Trigger integration page else, create a new one by sending a command /newbot to @BotFather Authorize the entire settings. Click on Next for further integration settings ahead. Click on the drop-down & select the specific chat list you have created earlier on Telegram. A. Sometimes you may not find the lists of your telegram account. One thing you can do that – go to your telegram account, then remove the administrator’s bot from that specific list or group & add again the administrator’s bot. B. To remove the bot & re-add the bot follow the path: Click on your desired list/group/Channel => Go to settings of that list/group/Channel => Administrator => Remove the promoted bot & add again the administrator’s bot Select the parse_mode method to send text notifications to the specified group or channel. You can use either HTML or Markdown format to send a message. Now, type a message as your preference. You can select Form Fields to fetch the user information if you want. Also, you can mention any group or channels from this message field.

You can select the action Attachment right below the Message’ field. Enabling this action, you can send – Audio, Video, Photo, or Document from Trigger to Telegram. After this, click on the Next option.
To successfully integrate your form with Telegram click the Finish & Save button. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

documents.t: Note: Zoho Marketing Hub is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Zoho Marketing Hub from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho Marketing Hub”. Select a data center from the dropdown. Then click on the Zoho API Console. Navigate to API Console-> Get Started-> Server-based Applications. Fill those fields (Homepage URL and Authorized Redirect URLs) the same as your Integration Homepage. Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Integrations integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select the list for the lead collection from the drop-down. Before that make sure you have already created a list on your marketing hub account. When you fill-up the contact list field, you will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related Zoho Marketing Hub. After clicking on Finish & Save, the Mailchimp integration is ready. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: Zoho Bigin is only available on the pro version. Search & Select Zoho Bigin from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho Bigin”. Select a data center from the dropdown. Then click on the Zoho API Console. Navigate to API Console-> Get Started-> Server-based Applications. Fill those fields (Homepage URL and Authorized Redirect URLs) the same as your Integration Homepage. Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Trigger integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select a Module from the drop-down list. Map all the mandatory Recruit fields to the corresponding fields in your form.

Workflow: Select this option to trigger the Zoho Bigin workflow for the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho Bigin workflow for the selected module doesn’t work. Attachment: To Select this option you can send file upload field data to Zoho Bigin related list Attachments. You can also send file upload field data to Zoho Bigin via normal field mapping). Please select the CRM file upload field from the drop-down which you want to send data. Approval: Select this option to automatically send form data to your Zoho Bigin approval list instead of adding them. Add Note: Select this action to add a note from Trigger to Zoho Bigin account automatically. Upload Photo: You can update any contact’s profile photo through our Trigger to your Zoho Bigin account. For that, hoover on the action called “Upload Photo“. After mapping the relevant fields, click the action ‘Upload Photo’ to upload a photo from Trigger to Zoho Bigin. Now click on ‘Save’. Whenever the user fills-up the form on Trigger, the image will be automatically uploaded as a profile photo to the Zoho Bigin account.

After giving all the required information, click on Finish & Save. Now your created Zoho Bigin API is ready for implementation. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: Zoho CRM is available on the free and pro version. Search & Select Zoho CRM from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho CRM”. Select a data center from the dropdown. Then click on the Zoho API Console. Navigate to API Console-> Get Started-> Server-based Applications. Fill those fields (Homepage URL and Authorized Redirect URLs) the same as your Integration Homepage. Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Integrations integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select a Module and Layout from the drop-down list. Map all the mandatory CRM fields to the corresponding fields in your form.

You can send data Zoho CRM related list from Trigger. Select the required related list module and layout from the drop-down provided. Then map the mandatory field. To map more fields, click on the (+).

Map all the fields, select the necessary Actions to be performed on integration, and then click on the Save button to save your settings. All the actions are described below. Workflow: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Attachment: To Select this option you can send file upload field data to Zoho CRM related list Attachments. You can also send file upload field data to Zoho CRM via normal field mapping). Please select the CRM file upload field from the drop-down which you want to send data. Approval: Select this option to automatically send form data to your Zoho CRM approval list instead of adding them. Blueprint: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Upsert Record: Upon selecting the option YES, if a record with the identical value exists in Zoho CRM, it will be updated with the new values. If you select NO, a new record will be created in Zoho CRM. You can arrange fields in the order in which upsert should happen. The record will update based on email address. Assignment Rules: When you choose this option, Assignment Rules defined in Zoho CRM can be triggered when form entries are added to a CRM module. Please select the assignment rule from the drop-down which you want to trigger. Tag Records: When you choose this option, you can add a tag to the records that are pushed to Zoho CRM. It helps you to search for records in CRM by tag. There has a list of tag records in the dropdown. You can use Zoho CRM by default tag, form fields also can add a custom tag. Record Owner: Select this option you can set a record owner of the sent record.
After clicking on Finish & Save, the Zoho CRM integration is ready. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

Note: Zoho CRM is available on the free and pro version. Search & Select Zoho CRM from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho CRM”. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Integrations integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select a Module and Layout from the drop-down list. Map all the mandatory CRM fields to the corresponding fields in your form.

You can send data Zoho CRM related list from Trigger. Select the required related list module and layout from the drop-down provided. Then map the mandatory field. To map more fields, click on the (+).

Map all the fields, select the necessary Actions to be performed on integration, and then click on the Save button to save your settings. All the actions are described below. Workflow: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Attachment: To Select this option you can send file upload field data to Zoho CRM related list Attachments. You can also send file upload field data to Zoho CRM via normal field mapping). Please select the CRM file upload field from the drop-down which you want to send data. Approval: Select this option to automatically send form data to your Zoho CRM approval list instead of adding them. Blueprint: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Upsert Record: Upon selecting the option YES, if a record with the identical value exists in Zoho CRM, it will be updated with the new values. If you select NO, a new record will be created in Zoho CRM. You can arrange fields in the order in which upsert should happen. The record will update based on email address. Assignment Rules: When you choose this option, Assignment Rules defined in Zoho CRM can be triggered when form entries are added to a CRM module. Please select the assignment rule from the drop-down which you want to trigger. Tag Records: When you choose this option, you can add a tag to the records that are pushed to Zoho CRM. It helps you to search for records in CRM by tag. There has a list of tag records in the dropdown. You can use Zoho CRM by default tag, form fields also can add a custom tag. Record Owner: Select this option you can set a record owner of the sent record.
After clicking on Finish & Save, the Zoho CRM integration is ready. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

documents.t: Select Typebot As A trigger Note: Typebot is available on the free and pro version. At First, Open your Bit Integration Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integration” button. Now select the Typebot that you want to integrate with Bit Integrations Actions. Bit integrations will automatically generate a webhook URL & you have to copy that link. And click on the fetch button. Now navigate to typebot dashboard -> select your typebot -> Add integration(webhook) -> click on configure . Paste the copied Webhook URL into the URL field. Click on to Test the request button. Then go to the Bit integration page and click on the set action button. info After completing these steps, the Actions list will appear, and select the action you want to integrate with your selected Trigger. Now you have to authorize the Action. To know more about authorization, Go to Actions from the left side menu and select the Action you want to integrate with your chosen trigger.

documents.t: Responses of the report manage submission data properly. Information gathered using a form needs to be presented for viewing. Once the form is successfully submitted, data will be added as a new row into the responses of the database when you hit the button of the form. We can easily manage, delete, update, filter, clone, and duplicate records. The features are shown below: ✔ View:/Detail View ✔ Column Reorder ✔ Adjustable Column Width ✔ Delete, Edit and duplicate ✔ Column Visibility ✔ Export Data

You can also view a maximum of 100 records on a single page. You can go next and previous pages by a single click. To the bottom right corner of the response page there is a option for showing a specific number of records on each page. Moreover, you can also sort record. If you click on any specific record you will see the record details as popup details views to the left.

You can easily reorder column by just dragging and dropping the mouse over the column title. If you have a column name First Name on the first column and Last Name on the second column. Now you can alter their position. If you hover the mouse over the column title, an option will be available to reorder respective column positions’ back and forth.
You can easily adjust column width by dragging your mouse onto it.

You can delete, edit, update or duplicate a specific record. You can also delete, duplicate and edit Bulk records.If you go to the very left of every specific record and click on three dots. You will find there the options will be available for delete, edit or duplicate. Suppose, you have two records with the same email = “test@test.com” so you can click on the record and delete the desired one. If you have 2000 records in your response and you want to delete them. For this you can select the multiple records together and click on the delete button to delete them together. This way you can delete all records from responses in a few attempts. You do not need to go through every record and delete them one by one.

You can easily hide and show columns in a single click of mouse. Suppose, you have many fields in your form and you want to show a few fields of them like First Name ➤ Last Name ➤ Phone ➤ Message. On the left side of responses you see an Eye icon. Just click on it and you will see all the fields will be available. You can put check mark only the fields you want to show and others keep unchecked.

You can export all the responses management data by clicking Export Data. When you click on Export data, a new window will be displayed where you will find 5 fields. These fields allow you to choose rows you want to export from Bit Form. Follow the below instructions: ➤ Click on export data from Form Responses & a window will be shown. ➤ How many rows to export: There you will find two options from the drop-down menu. Options are : All & Choose input number. You can export all rows or you can input row numbers as you want. If you select Choose input number then another field Enter your row number will arrive. ➤ Sort By: You can sort data in ascending or descending order. ➤ Select the sort field: You have to choose the fields that you want to sort. ➤ Export file format: You can choose 9 types of form to which you will export all data. Formats are : CSV, Xlsx, Xls, Fods, Ods, Prn, Text, HTML & Eth. ➤ Export all fields: If you want to export all the fields of the row then click on Yes or you can specify the fields you need to export by clicking No.

Search & Select wooCommerce from the actions pages Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken wooCommerce integration. Now, click on the connect button to complete authorization settings. Click on Next to set up the other integration settings ahead.

After the authorization process, select the module as Customer to create a customer account on site. When you select the module, you will see the Map Fields option where two fields- Email & Username, are mapped by default. You can map multiple fields according to your choice for the customer module. And click on the Next button to move forward for further settings. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button

After the authorization process, Select the module as Product if you're going to create any products on the site. Then map the necessary form fields with required WooCommerce fields from the Map Fields option. You can only create Simple Product & Affiliate Product. When you map all the form fields, you have to remember some default values on WooCommerce fields. So, you have to mention those values on the back end of the form builder. Which are: Product status - pending, draft, publish, future, private & trash. Product type - simple, external Allow Backorders - no, notify, yes Allow Reviews - open, closed Virtual - yes, no Manage Stock - yes, no Sold Individually - yes, no Downloadable - yes, no info The values are case-sensitive, so make sure to give it the same value as all small letters. You can customize the product categories & tags according to your choice from integration. Also, you can use the default options here. All the categories will be parent type. tip If any of the category or tags already exist in your WoocCommerce, then it will be referenced to that particular category/tag, otherwise it will create a new one. If you select the downloadable product, then you have to add attachment file fields. For this, you have to map the form field from the Map file upload fields section which is Downloadable Files. And click on the Next button to move forward for further settings. Now save the integration by clicking the Finish & Save Button
We have an option in every integration Timeline where you can check integration success or error status. Also, you can Edit Clone Delete the integration.
